
@startuml

class School {
  -name: String
  -rooms: Set<Room>
  -principals: Set<Teacher>
}

class Teacher {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
  -teachingRelationships: Set<TeachingRelationship>
}

class Student {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -classGroup: ClassGroup
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
  -students: Set<Student>
  -classroom: Classroom
}

class Classroom {
  -name: String
  -capacity: Integer
  -classGroups: Set<ClassGroup>
}

class Room {
  -name: String
  -size: Double
}

class Gym extends Room {
  -type: String
}

class TeachingRelationship {
  -hours: Integer
  -teacher: Teacher
  -school: School
}

School "1" -- "0..*" TeachingRelationship : has
TeachingRelationship "1" -- "1" Teacher : involves
TeachingRelationship "1" -- "1" School : involves

School "1" -- "1" Teacher : principal (only one)
Teacher "1" -- "0..1" School : can be principal of

Student "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : belongs to
ClassGroup "1" -- "1" Classroom : assigned to
Classroom "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : contains

Room "1" -- "1" School : part of
Gym "1" -- "1" Room : is a type of

@enduml

### Notes:
- **`School`** has a name and contains rooms and principals.
- **`Teacher`** has first name, last name, and email, and may have multiple teaching relationships with schools.
- **`Student`** has first and last name and belongs to exactly one **`ClassGroup`**.
- **`ClassGroup`** has a name, contains students, and is assigned to a **`Classroom`**.
- **`Classroom`** is a type of **`Room`**, which also includes other types like **`Gym`**.
- **`TeachingRelationship`** connects a teacher to a school and records the number of hours they teach there.
- A **`School`** has **exactly one principal**, who is a **`Teacher`**.
- A **`Teacher`** can be the principal of **at most one school**.
- A **`ClassGroup`** consists of **10–31 students** and is assigned to **one classroom**, and vice versa.

